{
  "stem": "7744.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I also am not quite sure how long Bergen-Belsen as a camp really existed in the kind of situation that it did at the time.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I think that when one talks to people who were in Bergen-Belsen-- and I don't discuss it with people too much.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There are more pleasant things for me to talk to people-- but when I do, then people are saying to me how horrible it was.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother died just a couple of weeks before liberation.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then I was alone, maybe two, three weeks before.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was liberated by the Swedish Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think it's Count Bernadotte who came into-- into the camp and liberated the children.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There weren't that many children.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I-- I have a picture, in fact, of some of the children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was not the youngest, but there weren't too many younger than myself.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After liberation, I was taken to Sweden to Malmo.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were put into a hostel-- more like a hospital hostel.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I-- I must have weighed-- maybe, I don't know-- maybe 50 pounds.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had tuberculosis, and I had typhoid, and-- and my head was shaven, and so I was quite a sight.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was in Sweden in several hostels.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was in Malmo for a little while for a few months, and I got a little better.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then they sent us to a hostel where there were children.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE] came from Israel, and the people from the Jewish agency in Sweden and around the world came and helped the children.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there we had the [INAUDIBLE] teach us and get us supposedly ready for some normality, whatever that was going to be.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And some of these children eventually left for Israel.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so in Sweden, life was wonderful.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
